                            <comment id="145756" author="jgmitter" created="Wed, 16 Mar 2016 13:57:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Need to reopen/resolve again to fix the Resolution status to be &quot;Not a bug&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="105498" author="liang" created="Tue, 3 Feb 2015 14:09:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;sorry I was wrong, lnet_parse() will not LBUG on unknown message type,  lnet_parse has two places that check message type, at the begin of lnet_parse, it returns EPROTO for unknown message type, there is another code block which LBUG for unknown message type, but it should never happen. So I think we can close this ticket.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="105496" author="liang" created="Tue, 3 Feb 2015 13:44:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;yes, this should be a simple patch, I will work it out soon.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
